      "content": "# most state schema fields should be optional to support empty documents\n\nDocuments are created empty and populated through operations. If the state schema requires fields that are not set at creation time, the initial state will violate the schema.\n\n```graphql\n// ✅ Optional fields — document can be created empty\ntype InvoiceState {\n    recipient: String\n    amount: Amount_Money\n    dueDate: Date\n}\n\n// ❌ Too many required fields — empty document fails validation\ntype InvoiceState {\n    recipient: String!\n    amount: Amount_Money!\n    dueDate: Date!\n}\n```\n\nUse `!` only for fields that genuinely cannot be absent, like arrays (since [[arrays in state schemas must use mandatory notation]]) or fields set at document creation time.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
